  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is cooking, add your <strong>butternut squash cubes</strong> to a heatproof bowl</p><p>Cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until the squash is fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Grate your <strong>chestnut</strong> <strong>mushrooms</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the lardons are crisp, add the <strong>cooked butternut squash cubes </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until starting to brown, reserve the bowl</p><p>Once the butternut has started to brown, add the <strong>grated mushrooms</strong>, <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>dried sage </strong>(not a fan of sage? Just add a little!) and cook for 4-5 min or until all the liquid has evaporated – this is your <strong>vegetable mix</strong></p><p>Once done, transfer the <strong>vegetable mix </strong>to the reserved bowl, reserve the pan</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>with 300ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>bay leaf[ves] </strong>and 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml] </span><strong>milk </strong>– this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat, once hot, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock </strong>gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains, season with a generous pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your<strong> béchamel</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>vegetable mix </strong>to the <strong>béchamel </strong>– this is your <strong>lasagne filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>lasagne filling</strong> over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with some of your <strong>lasagne sheets</strong>, being careful not to overlap the sheets</p><p>Repeat this process until you end up with a final layer of lasagne filling (you may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish)</p><p>Top with your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook in the oven for 30 min or until the pasta is cooked</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-butternut-lasagne-with-mushroom-and-sage/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lasagne</strong> with the <strong>washed salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Dress the salad with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
